Code Review
===========

Code reviews try to ensure that the code in an area is up-to-date,
internally consistent, consistent with mudwide standards, and have an
acceptable style. There is no excuse for new code that is just as bad
as the bad old stuff we already have.

When doing a code review, the reviewer should recognize that the code
should be in an acceptable style, not necessarily the reviewer's own.
Whatever the personal style of the area coder, the format of the code
should be reasonably readable to someone not familiar with the area.
Note that the code should update before even getting to this stage, and
it's expected that the code is already tested to work as intended.

